stage directions. No actions in parentheses or brackets.\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1181:- NEVER prefix the line with an action description. Do NOT begin \r\nwith words\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1182:  like \"twirls his pen\", \"clenches jaw\", \"pauses, sets pen down\". \r\nStart the\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1183:  output directly with the first spoken word.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1184:- No \"he said\" / \"she added\" / narration of any kind.\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1185:- Output the single line and stop. Nothing before it, nothing \r\nafter.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1186:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1187:CRAFT:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1188:- Imply more than you state. People rarely say what they mean.\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1189:- Push the scene forward by one small step.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1190:- Follow naturally from the last thing said.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1191:- Stay in the speaker's voice - their job, their pressure, their \r\nhabits.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1202:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1203:\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1204:def _format_last_lines(last_lines: list[tuple[str, str]]) -> str:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1205:    \"\"\"Render the rolling-window of recent dialogue.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1206:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1207:    Phase 4 v4 (2026-05-11): label moved from \"RECENT DIALOGUE\" to\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1208:    \"LAST SPOKEN (this scene)\" at the call site. Empty window now\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:1209