silently never \r\nstamped\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2877:# (BUG-LOCAL-255).\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2878:#\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2879:# Two purpose-built creative-slot passes replace both surfaces:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2880:#   compose_announcer_intro  -- in-loop on the first announcer \r\nbeat;\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2881:#                               a framing prompt from \r\nscript_brief.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2882:#   compose_announcer_outro  -- post-loop on the last announcer \r\nbeat;\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2883:#                               a closing prompt from \r\nscript_brief +\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2884:#                               news_close_brief + the intro text.\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2885:# Both bypass `compose_line` (so they are never re-polished -- \r\ncorrect\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2886:# by construction) and emit plain text, not JSON: a one-line \r\noutput\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2887:# does not need a JSON envelope, and the envelope only adds a\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2888:# broken-JSON failure mode. Each pass has a deterministic SIGNAL \r\nLOST\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2889:# fallback so the narrative bookend can never be missing.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2890:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2891:# Generation params for the announcer passes. One creative call \r\neach,\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2892:# no reroll ladder -- on any failure the deterministic fallback \r\nfires.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2893:_ANNOUNCER_MAX_NEW_TOKENS = 160\r\n  production_mirr