mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2948:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2949:OUTPUT - strict:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2950:- Only the words the announcer says out loud.\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2951:- One line. No line breaks.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2952:- No speaker name, no colon, no quotation marks.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2953:- No stage directions, no brackets, no sound cues.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2956:VOICE:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2957:- A period radio host: warm, measured, reflective.\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2958:- Land the journalistic note from the closing brief.\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2959:- Lightly echo the opening line's tone; do not repeat its words.\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2960:- Use only proper names that appear in the briefs. Invent none.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2961:- CLOSE ON A CONCRETE FINAL IMAGE: show what physically changed \r\n-- a person,\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2962:  an object, a place. Do NOT state a moral, lesson, or \r\nnews-summary (\"the\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2963:  lesson is\", \"reminding us\", \"tonight's revelation\", \"this \r\nshows\").\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2964:\"\"\"\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2965:\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2966:\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2967:def clean_one_line(text: str, max_chars: int) -> str:\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2968:    \"\"\"Collapse a raw string into a single clean line.\r\n  production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2969:\r\n> production_mirror\\nodes\\_otr_line_composer.py:2970:    