prompt before editing.\r\n41:2. Preserve current shipped behavior under `sci_fi_radio`.\r\n42:3. Add visual-style policy reads at shared seams first.\r\n43:4. Only then replace deep fallback prompts one by one.\r\n44:5. Test each style for forbidden phrase leakage.\r\n45:\r\n46:Do not assume one new visual-style node can cleanly override every downstream\r\n47:image/video prompt. R3 must plan this as a transplant with risk checkpoints.\r\n48:\r\n49:## Future Bridge Strategy\r\n50:\r\n51:The lab should grow an upstream translator head before it touches the full\r\n52:production downstream workflow.\r\n53:\r\n54:Planned boundary:\r\n55:\r\n56:```text\r\n57:upstream_story_lab source/story/visual spec\r\n58:-> translator head\r\n59:-> bridge node or bridge adapter\r\n60:-> latest production OTR downstream workflow\r\n61:```\r\n62:\r\n63:The bridge is not the first build. The first build proves the upstream\r\n64:translator can produce a validated production-ledger-shaped payload from fixture\r\n65:source packets and prompt profiles.\r\n66:\r\n67:Only after that:\r\n68:\r\n69:1. add a bridge adapter/node plan\r\n70:2. generate a dry-run patch plan for production code and workflow JSON\r\n71:3. review widget deltas and forceInput sockets\r\n72:4. apply the transplant in one explicit chunk\r\n73:5. run focused integration tests before any full e2e render\r\n74:\r\n75:Until the translator head is ready, do not run full e2e tests through the bridge\r\n76:and do not wire the bridge into `workflows/otr_scifi_16gb_full.json`.\r\n77:\r\n78:## Future Source-Bank Dropdown\r\n79:\r\n80:Planned source-bank dropdown labels:\r\n81:\r\n82:- `science_news`: \"Sci-Fi Science News\"\r\n83:- `media_archive`: \"Media RSS / Archive\"\r\n84:- `public_domain_story`: \"Public Domain\"\r\n85:- `custom_source_bank`: \"+ Add Your Own\"\r\n86:\r\n87:Suggested tooltip for `custom_source_bank`:\r\n88:\r\n89:```text\r\n90:Build a custom source bank from a schema/profile. See upstream_story_lab/CUSTOM_SOURCE_BANK_GUIDE.md.\r\n91:```\r\n92:\r\n93:`custom_source_bank` must not silently run anything. If selected without a valid\r\n94:custom schema/profile, it raises a clear error pointing to the guide.\r\n95:\r\n96:## Future Transplant Script\r\n97:\r\n98:A future Python transplant helper is allowed, but it must be dry-run first and\r\n99:manifest-driven.\r\n100:\r\n101:Expected shape:\r\n102:\r\n103:```text\r\n104:scripts/plan_transplant.py --dry-run\r\n105:scripts/plan_transplant.py --apply --manifest <approved-manifest.json>\r\n106:```\r\n107:\r\n108:It should be able to propose or apply:\r\n109:\r\n110:- prompt-profile code edits\r\n111:- visual-style policy hook edits\r\n112:- workflow JSON widget appends\r\n113:- bridge node insertion\r\n114:- link creation for forceInput policy sockets\r\n115:- whitelist updates in `scripts/otr_api.py`\r\n116:- whitelist updates in `nodes/_otr_workflow_apply.py`\r\n117:\r\n118:Hard rule: the script must refuse to apply unless the manifest names every file,\r\n119:expected widget-vector delta, and validation command. No silent broad rewrite.\r\n120:\r\n121:## Workflow JSON Touch Rules\r\n122:\r\n123:When the transplant reaches workflow wiring:\r\n124:\r\n125:- edit only `workflows/otr_scifi_16gb_full.json`\r\n126:- append widgets only\r\n127:- use forceInput sockets for linked policy JSON\r\n128:- run the workflow validator\r\n129:- run JSON round-trip validation\r\n130:- run link referential integrity audit\r\n131:- run widget/input audit\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_20","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\WINDOWS\\\\System32\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\v1.0\\\\powershell.exe\" -Command '$i=0; Get-Content '\"'kibitz-runs\\\\2026-07-02-upstream-transplant-v2\\\\r1\\\\input.md' | ForEach-Object { \"'$i++; if($i -le 260){ '\"'{0}:{1}' -f \"'$i,$_ } }'","aggregated_output":"1:# R1 Architecture + Coding Plan v2 - Upstream Multi-Source Story Engine\r\n2:\r\n3:Date: 2026-07-02 (overnight run). Author: Claude Fable R1 pass.\r\n4:Workspace: ComfyUI-OTR-UpstreamStoryLab (transplant workspace).\r\n5:Baseline: production_mirror @ ComfyUI-OldTimeRadio d48a9d76 (SFX-free).\r\n6:Prior art: v1 lab (git 41c6512), FABLE_FINAL_REVIEW_2026-07-02.md.\r\n7:Write scope: THIS FOLDER ONLY. Production is not edited until the explicit\r\n8:transplant chunk.\r\n9:\r\n10:Core law (unchanged, now enforced structurally):\r\n11:\r\n12:```text\r\n13:JSON owns content and configuration.\r\n14:Python owns validation, routing, execution, and fail-loud errors.\r\n15:No fallbacks. No hidden models. No hidden engines.\r\n16:```\r\n17:\r\n18:## 1. The architecture in one picture\r\n19:\r\n20:```text\r\n21:banks.json ---------+\r\n22:story packs (JSON) -+-> REGISTRY (loaded, validated, fail-loud)\r\n23:visual styles (JSON)+        |\r\n24:pipelines (JSON) ---+        v\r\n25:                     resolve(source_bank, story_model, story_pipeline, visual_style)\r\n26:                             |            [every id explicit or declared default;\r\n27:                             |             unknown/ambiguous = hard error]\r\n28:source packet (JSON/fetch) --+\r\n29:                             v\r\n30:                     SourceInterpreter[bank]   <- declared binding, allowlisted\r\n31:                             |                    (science = news_interpreter at\r\n32:                             v                     transplant; fixtures in lab)\r\n33:                     StoryInputPacket\r\n34:                             v\r\n35:                     LedgerWritingSpec  (spec = ids + material + story input\r\n36:                             |           + prompt profile + visual policy +\r\n37:                             |           model plan; cross-id validated)\r\n38:                             v\r\n39:                     BRIDGE ARTIFACT (one frozen JSON file)\r\n40:                       - ledger_writing_spec\r\n41:                       - meta_mirrors: news (NewsBriefs shape), news_seed\r\n42:                       - lab_state_digest + schema_version + baseline hash\r\n43:                             v\r\n44:                     production adapter (tomorrow's transplant chunk)\r\n45:```\r\n46:\r\n47:## 2. Axes, precisely separated\r\n48:\r\n49:Four orthogonal axes; each is data, none may imply another silently:\r\n50:\r\n51:- `source_bank` - where material comes from and how it is interpreted.\r\n52:  Declared in `fixtures/banks.json`. Adding a bank touches zero routing code.\r\n53:- `story_model` - dramatic/tonal writing lane, source-scoped. One JSON pack\r\n54:  per (bank, model, pipeline). Adding a model = dropping a pack file.\r\n55:- `story_pipeline` - the LLM pass structure. Declared in\r\n56:  `fixtures/pipelines.json` as a named sequence of passes with per-pass slot\r\n57:  roles (creative/technical), seam references, and hard budgets. Python owns\r\n58:  sequencing, stop conditions, and failure reporting; JSON owns the sequence\r\n59:  and prompts.\r\n60:- `visual_style` - render language. One JSON policy per style. Role-keyed\r\n61:  motion prompts validated against the production role vocabulary.\r\n62:\r\n63:Bank/model/style defaults are configuration -> they live in `banks.json`\r\n64:(`default_story_model`, `default_visual_style`), not in Python dicts.\r\n65:\r\n66:## 3. No hidden models, no hidden engines - made structural\r\n67:\r\n68:- Every LLM-touching pass in a pipeline declares its slot role\r\n69:  (`creative` | `technical`) in `pipelines.json`. The spec carries the\r\n70:  resolved `model_plan` so the ledger can stamp what ran. No pass may call a\r\n71:  model without a declaration.\r\n72:- Every Python behavior a bank needs (fetcher, interpreter) is a NAMED\r\n73:  binding string in `banks.json` (e.g. `\"interpreter\": \"fixture_media_archive\"`,\r\n74:  at transplant `\"science_rss_news_interpreter\"`). Python resolves bindings\r\n75:  through one explicit allowlist registry; an undeclared or unknown binding\r\n76:  is a hard error with the bank id in the message.\r\n77:- The adaptive-cleanup experiment's approved technical models are a JSON\r\n78:  allowlist (`pipelines.json`), enforced by Python; the cap\r\n79:  (`max_cleanup_passes`) is JSON config, the stop condition is Python.\r\n80:- Ledger stamps at transplant: `meta.source_bank`, `meta.story_model`,\r\n81:  `meta.story_pipeline`, `meta.visual_style` (+ mirrors). Nothing runs\r\n82:  unlabeled.\r\n83:\r\n84:## 4. One prompt vocabulary: seams\r\n85:\r\n86:v1 had two overlapping content vocabularies (pack `prompt_stages` dict AND\r\n87:`StoryPromptProfile` fields). v2 defines ONE canonical seam list, matching\r\n88:the production prompt sites the transplant will parameterize:\r\n89:\r\n90:```text\r\n91:interpret            (source brain -> briefs; science keeps news_interpreter)\r\n92:outline_system\r\n93:pitch_room_system\r\n94:story_select_system\r\n95:dramatic_state_system\r\n96:line_grounding       (per-line instruction)\r\n97:casting_brief_seam   (source/casting brief text path; craft stays shared)\r\n98:coda                 (coda_mode + coda_system + examples)\r\n99:title_system\r\n100:style_pick_inventor\r\n101:style_pick_chooser   (+ chooser_user_template)\r\n102:labels               (story_form_label, source_material_label,\r\n103:                      source_develop_verb, source_grounding_label,\r\n104:                      key_terms_label, close_brief_label, title_form_label)\r\n105:```\r\n106:\r\n107:A story pack supplies seam content + guardrails + forbidden lists.\r\n108:`StoryPromptProfile` is now a RESOLVED VIEW built by validating and merging\r\n109:(pack + bank defaults). It contains no Python-authored prose. If a seam is\r\n110:missing and the bank declares it required, loading fails loudly - no default\r\n111:prose is invented.\r\n112:\r\n113:Forbidden-term handling stays metadata (leakage tests scan rendered\r\n114:previews; forbidden phrases are never rendered into live prompts - models\r\n115:copy negated terms).\r\n116:\r\n117:## 5. Compatibility mirrors as pinned, drift-proof contracts\r\n118:\r\n119:`src/upstream_story_lab/compat.py` pins the production shapes:\r\n120:\r\n121:- `NEWS_BRIEFS_FIELDS` = exact NewsBriefs field list (casting_brief,\r\n122:  script_brief, news_close_brief, key_terms, source_hash, source_chars,\r\n123:  prompt_version, schema_version, model_id, decoder_profile, seed, attempts,\r\n124:  attempt_failures) - cited to production_mirror/nodes/news_interpreter.py.\r\n125:- `NEWS_SEED_KEYS` = {headline, source, url, date, body_chars, style,\r\n126:  selected_at} - cited to production_mirror/nodes/_otr_legacy_to_stage1_adapter.py.\r\n127:- `MOTION_ROLE_KEYS` = {announcer, music_open, music_close, music_inter} -\r\n128:  cited to production_mirror/nodes/_otr_video_engines/render_driver.py.\r\n129:- `SCI_FI_TAILS` = STYLE_TAIL_DEFAULT / IMAGE_GRADE_TAIL /\r\n130:  RADIO_BROADCAST_TAIL / ERA_TAIL_DEFAULT strings - cited to\r\n131:  production_mirror/nodes/_otr_story_brief_helpers.py.\r\n132:\r\n133:Drift-proofing (the advanced part): tests AST-parse the mirrored production\r\n134:files and EXTRACT these shapes (NewsBriefs class fields, the news_seed dict\r\n135:literal keys, `_LTX_MOTION_PROMPT_BY_ROLE` keys, the tail constants), then\r\n136:assert the pinned copies match. Re-mirroring after production moves makes\r\n137:any shape drift a test failure, not a silent bug. `key_terms` is always a\r\n138:list (freeze invariant, _otr_ledger_freeze.py).\r\n139:\r\n140:The bridge emits `meta_mirrors = {news: <NewsBriefs shape>, news_seed:\r\n141:<seed shape>}`. `meta.news = None` degrade semantics stay a production\r\n142:decision; the bridge always emits a complete mirror.\r\n143:\r\n144:## 6. Visual policy, production-shaped\r\n145:\r\n146:`VisualStylePolicy` v2:\r\n147:\r\n148:- `positive_tail`, `image_grade_tail`, `broadcast_tail`, `era_tail` -\r\n149:  policy-owned replacements for the four production constants.\r\n150:- `allow_radio_tails`, `forbidden_terms` (leakage-test fodder, never\r\n151:  rendered).\r\n152:- subjects: announcer / music / scene_open / character_portrait /\r\n153:  character_scene.\r\n154:- `motion_prompts` keyed ONLY by `MOTION_ROLE_KEYS` (validator rejects\r\n155:  unknown keys - scene_broll/background_abstract/sfx are dead roles and must\r\n156:  stay dead).\r\n157:- `sci_fi_radio` policy must reproduce the production tails byte-identically\r\n158:  (test compares against the AST-extracted constants) - this IS the science\r\n159:  visual baseline pin.\r\n160:\r\n161:## 7. What gets CODED tonight (lab-only)\r\n162:\r\n163:C1 `src/upstream_story_lab/` v2 package:\r\n164:   - `contracts.py` - pydantic v2 models, extra=forbid: SourceMaterialPacket,\r\n165:     PublicDomainSourceManifest, StoryPack (seam-complete), SourceBankSpec,\r\n166:     PipelineSpec, StoryPromptProfile (resolved view), StoryInputPacket,\r\n167:     VisualStylePolicy, LedgerWritingSpec (cross-id validators), BridgeArtifact.\r\n168:   - `compat.py` - pinned production shapes + citations.\r\n169:   - `registry.py` - loads banks/packs/styles/pipelines from fixtures/,\r\n170:     duplicate/unknown/missing = hard error, zero content literals,\r\n171:     binding allowlist for interpreters.\r\n172:   - `interpreters.py` - fixture interpreters per bank (deterministic,\r\n173:     network-free), same protocol production brains will implement.\r\n174:   - `profiles.py` - pack -> profile resolution (validation only).\r\n175:   - `bridge.py` - spec assembly + bridge artifact emit/refuse + mirrors.\r\n176:   - `preview.py` - prompt preview rendering + pack-driven leakage scan\r\n177:     (every non-science bank, not just media archive).\r\n178:C2 `fixtures/` - banks.json, pipelines.json, 12 story packs (recovered from\r\n179:   git v1 and extended to seam-complete; diverged v1 Python/JSON lists\r\n180:   reconciled by union), 5 visual styles (motion keys re-keyed), source\r\n181:   packets (fixture briefs moved INTO packets), PD source folders,\r\n182:   custom-bank schema template.\r\n183:C3 `tests/` - contracts, registry fail-loud/no-fallback, leakage (story +\r\n184:   visual), mirror drift-proof (AST vs pinned), sci-fi tail byte-pin,\r\n185:   motion-key validation, bridge emit/refuse, PD manifest safety\r\n186:   (absolute/.. paths), pipeline sequencing + loud pass failure.\r\n187:C4 `nodes.py` + `scripts/validate_lab.py` - ComfyUI validator/preview nodes\r\n188:   and CLI runner rebuilt on v2 (choices discovered from JSON, never\r\n189:   hardcoded lists).\r\n190:C5 `transplant_work/` - staged production edits, lab-only:\r\n191:   - NEW modules as real files (production-ready, no imports from lab):\r\n192:     `_otr_source_interpreter.py` (facade; science delegates to\r\n193:     news_interpreter unchanged), `_otr_story_prompt_profile.py`,\r\n194:     `_otr_visual_style_policy.py`, `_otr_ledger_input_adapter.py`\r\n195:     (bridge-artifact validator).\r\n196:   - PATCH SPECS (exact before/after hunks, file+line cited against\r\n197:     production_mirror) for the big files: OTR_LedgerScriptWriter (routing,\r\n198:     title, coda call sites, RSS gate to science_news, meta stamps,\r\n199:     append-only widgets), _otr_line_composer (compose_source_coda facade,\r\n200:     line grounding), _otr_style_picker (override kwargs, loud non-science\r\n201:     failure), _otr_story_brief_helpers + otr_meta_brief_image_prompt +\r\n202:     otr_shot_lock (policy seam reads), news_interpreter (science-only\r\n203:     confinement), whitelists (scripts/otr_api.py, _otr_workflow_apply.py).\r\n204:   - `workflows/otr_scifi_16gb_full.json` working copy: widget-append plan\r\n205:     documented, NOT applied until production tests exist (tomorrow).\r\n206:\r\n207:Priority order tonight: C1 -> C2 -> C3 green -> C4 -> C5 as far as context\r\n208:allows. Every chunk committed; single push at end.\r\n209:\r\n210:## 7b. Fable R1 delta - upgrades the prior rounds did not have\r\n211:\r\n212:These five are structural, cheap, and compose with the registry design.\r\n213:They are what makes this architecture verifiable rather than merely tidy.\r\n214:\r\n215:1. Template-variable validation at load time. Every seam prompt is a\r\n216:   template with a DECLARED variable set per seam (e.g. line_grounding may\r\n217:   reference {source_grounding_label}, {scene_premise}). The registry\r\n218:   string.Formatter-parses every template in every pack and fails loudly on\r\n219:   an undeclared or misspelled variable at LOAD, not mid-episode. A JSON\r\n220:   content system without this ships prompt typos silently.\r\n221:2. Auditable resolution. `resolve()` returns a Resolution record: requested\r\n222:   ids, resolved ids, which defaults applied, and the source file of every\r\n223:   decision. \"auto\" stops being invisible behavior and becomes data the\r\n224:   bridge artifact carries. Kills the hidden-default class structurally.\r\n225:3. Provenance stamping with content hashes. The spec/bridge carries\r\n226:   `provenance = {bank, model, pipeline, visual_style, pack_sha256,\r\n227:   style_sha256, banks_sha256, pipelines_sha256, lab_state_digest,\r\n228:   production_baseline}`. Any episode is reproducible and auditable back to\r\n229:   the exact JSON bytes that shaped it. At transplant this lands in ledger\r\n230:   meta beside the four id stamps.\r\n231:4. Cross-product invariant tests. The registry makes (bank x model x\r\n232:   pipeline x style) enumerable, so tests assert over ALL combos: resolution\r\n233:   succeeds or raises a typed error (never substitutes); non-science\r\n234:   previews never contain science/news terms; every template formats\r\n235:   cleanly against a fixture context; every declared binding exists in the\r\n236:   allowlist. This is the architectural proof of \"no hidden fallback\" -\r\n237:   not example-based, exhaustive.\r\n238:5. Pipeline simulation with failure injection. A FakeLLM runner executes\r\n239:   any declared pipeline end-to-end (network-free) and tests inject a\r\n240:   failure at each pass to assert the exact failing pass is reported and\r\n241:   nothing falls back. Plus `schema_version` on every fixture; the registry\r\n242:   refuses versions it does not know. No silent migration.\r\n243:\r\n244:Considered and rejected (deliberately, for this system's scale): agent-graph\r\n245:DSLs, content-addressed prompt stores, effect-system-style capability\r\n246:tokens, pack inheritance/merge trees. Each adds machinery a one-operator\r\n247:local pipeline does not need; rejection keeps \"clean\" honest. Single-level\r\n248:`extends` for packs is noted as a future option if pack count grows past ~30.\r\n249:\r\n250:## 8. Gates (unchanged from the final review, plus two)\r\n251:\r\n252:All gates in FABLE_FINAL_REVIEW_2026-07-02.md TEST/VALIDATION GATES, plus:\r\n253:\r\n254:- AST drift-proof tests pass against production_mirror (new).\r\n255:- sci_fi_radio visual policy byte-identical to production tails (new).\r\n256:\r\n257:## 9. Non-goals tonight\r\n258:\r\n259:- No production writes. No workflow JSON widget edits (plan only).\r\n260:- No LLM calls in lab tests (fixture interpreters are deterministic).\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
