ing_change, close)\r\n3658:          if resolved else fallback_announcer_outro(close))\r\n3659:    return LineResult(\r\n3660:        text=fb,\r\n3661:        compose_flags=(\"announcer_outro_fallback\",),\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_26","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\WINDOWS\\\\System32\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\v1.0\\\\powershell.exe\" -Command '$i=0; Get-Content '\"'production_mirror\\\\nodes\\\\OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py' | ForEach-Object { \"'$i++; if(($i -ge 121 -and $i -le 132) -or ($i -ge 5200 -and $i -le 5255) -or ($i -ge 5419 -and $i -le 5441)){ '\"'{0}:{1}' -f \"'$i,$_ } }'","aggregated_output":"121:# S30 B2a: catalog drives the dropdown_choices() for the two model widgets\r\n122:# at INPUT_TYPES() registration time. Pure-Python module, no torch /\r\n123:# transformers / GPU work -- safe at module-import time.\r\n124:from . import _otr_model_catalog as _otr_model_catalog  # noqa: E501\r\n125:\r\n126:# Sprint C C5a2 (2026-05-15) module-level import per E-22 / RR-B4. The\r\n127:# reflection pure module is wired into execute() at K.5.5 -- see the\r\n128:# reflection call site below the K.5 visual_plan stamp. Module-level\r\n129:# import (not hot-path) so a typo / refactor surfaces at module load\r\n130:# time rather than during the first script generation.\r\n131:from ._otr_story_brief import run_story_brief_reflection\r\n132:\r\n5200:\r\n5201:        # --- J.5. Post-composition title regen (late binding) ---------\r\n5202:        # Per Jeffrey 2026-05-10: when the user leaves episode_title\r\n5203:        # blank, regenerate the title from the FINAL story material via\r\n5204:        # the LLM. The prompt does NOT see the news_seed -- the title is\r\n5205:        # grounded purely in the finished episode. User-typed\r\n5206:        # episode_title still wins; LLM only fires on blank input;\r\n5207:        # outline.title is the last-resort fallback when the LLM call\r\n5208:        # fails or its output is rejected by the guardrails.\r\n5209:        #\r\n5210:        # Sprint 3E (2026-05-25) -- scratchpad + late binding:\r\n5211:        #  - The title is bound LATE, here, after the script exists.\r\n5212:        #    The per-line composer (section I) ran with `EPISODE_TITLE:\r\n5213:        #    TBD` in canon_header, so no provisional / outline title was\r\n5214:        #    ever placed where a beat could speak it. There is no \"old\r\n5215:        #    title\" baked into dialogue, so the fragile post-hoc\r\n5216:        #    verbatim string substitution (the former section J.6) is\r\n5217:        #    removed entirely -- it only caught verbatim quotes anyway\r\n5218:        #    and let paraphrases slip through.\r\n5219:        #  - `_generate_title_from_script` is now a forced-scratchpad\r\n5220:        #    pass (3 physical details -> 3 candidate titles -> final\r\n5221:        #    TITLE: line) reading the whole-arc excerpt set, not a thin\r\n5222:        #    head-of-script slice. The writer passes the outline\r\n5223:        #    premise as additional grounding (the story spine, not the\r\n5224:        #    news article). `arc_verdict` is left \"\" -- the Sprint 5B\r\n5225:        #    whole-script critic that would emit it is not built yet.\r\n5226:        title_source = \"outline_fallback\"\r\n5227:        if resolved[\"episode_title\"]:\r\n5228:            # User typed a value; respect it verbatim.\r\n5229:            final_title = resolved[\"episode_title\"]\r\n5230:            title_source = \"user\"\r\n5231:        else:\r\n5232:            assembled_script = \"\\n\\n\".join(script_text_parts).strip()\r\n5233:            # LLM slot: creative -- title regen is a narrative pass\r\n5234:            # (scratchpad: extract physical details, draft candidates,\r\n5235:            # commit a final title). One LLM call produces the whole\r\n5236:            # scratchpad + the parsed TITLE: line. Routed through the\r\n5237:            # writer's creative_writing_model slot; no widget.\r\n5238:            # Sprint 0 (v4 plan): helper_context attribution.\r\n5239:            with slot_scheduler.helper_context(\"generate_title\"):\r\n5240:                regen_title = _generate_title_from_script(\r\n5241:                    creative_generate_fn,\r\n5242:                    assembled_script,\r\n5243:                    temperature=resolved[\"temperature\"],\r\n5244:                    premise=outline.premise,\r\n5245:                    arc_verdict=\"\",\r\n5246:                )\r\n5247:            if regen_title:\r\n5248:                final_title = regen_title\r\n5249:                title_source = \"llm_post_composition\"\r\n5250:            else:\r\n5251:                final_title = outline.title\r\n5252:                title_source = \"outline_fallback\"\r\n5253:                log.warning(\r\n5254:                    \"[OTR_LedgerScriptWriter] title regen returned empty; \"\r\n5255:                    \"falling back to outline.title=%r\",\r\n5419:        # --- K.5.5. meta.story_brief reflection pass ------------------\r\n5420:        # Per Sprint C final plan Q1 lock (K.5.5, E-01). Writes to meta\r\n5421:        # only; lines untouched; runs on technical_model slot per L-2.\r\n5422:        # Failure path stamps story_brief_status per L-6 fail-loud\r\n5423:        # sentinel pattern. Refinement section 3.6 sync-barrier wording\r\n5424:        # was amended at C0b -- this call inherits the non-blocking\r\n5425:        # BUG-LOCAL-228 timeout contract via technical_generate_fn.\r\n5426:        #\r\n5427:        # Dual-slot OOM analysis (E-15 revised at C1 audit per RR-A1):\r\n5428:        # the loader is single-slot by architecture. request_slot(\r\n5429:        # technical_model) inside technical_generate_fn calls\r\n5430:        # unload_llm() to evict any prior resident model BEFORE loading\r\n5431:        # the next. Peak transient VRAM during the swap is max(\r\n5432:        # creative_size, technical_size), not their sum. No explicit\r\n5433:        # pre-eviction call is needed; regression tests in C5a2 prove\r\n5434:        # the no-OOM property.\r\n5435:        # LLM slot: technical\r\n5436:        # Sprint 0 (v4 plan): helper_context attribution.\r\n5437:        with slot_scheduler.helper_context(\"story_brief_reflection\"):\r\n5438:            _brief_delta = run_story_brief_reflection(\r\n5439:                led,\r\n5440:                technical_generate_fn,\r\n5441:                technical_model_id=resolved[\"technical_model\"],\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"VERDICT: no. The plan’s core story is “no hidden fallbacks, all LLM passes declared,” but it omits a live production LLM phase, conflicts with the repository’s transplant sequencing, and leaves source fetching/binding semantics underspecified.\n\nMUST-FIX BEFORE BUILD:\n1. [§4, §7 C1/C3] Missing LLM phase in the canonical seam/pipeline vocabulary. The plan says every LLM-touching pass is declared in `pipelines.json` and no pass may call a model without declaration (`kibitz-runs/2026-07-02-upstream-transplant-v2/r1/input.md:68-71`), but the seam list omits the live `story_brief_reflection` pass. Production calls `run_story_brief_reflection` through the technical slot at `production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:5419-5441`. Concrete fix: add a `story_brief_reflection` seam and pipeline pass, or explicitly disable/defer that production phase and add a test proving it is not reachable in the bridge path.\n\n2. [§1, §7 C5] The bridge/transplant arc contradicts the repo’s own staging rules. The plan sends the bridge artifact to a “production adapter (tomorrow’s transplant chunk)” (`input.md:39-44`) and includes production-ready modules plus patch specs in tonight’s C5 (`input.md:190-205`). `TRANSPLANT_MANIFEST.md` says the bridge is not the first build; the first build is a translator head, and bridge/wiring comes only after that (`TRANSPLANT_MANIFEST.md:49-76`). Concrete fix: split the arc into “lab translator/bridge artifact now” and “production adapter/patch specs later,” or update the manifest and gates before C5 is in scope.\n\n3. [§2, §3, §7 C1] Source-bank extensibility is overstated. The plan claims “Adding a bank touches zero routing code” (`input.md:51-52`), but also requires every bank behavior to be a named Python binding resolved through an allowlist (`input.md:72-76`), while C1 only lists fixture interpreters and no fetcher protocol (`input.md:169-173`). Concrete fix: define `SourceFetcher` and `SourceInterpreter` protocols, state that new behavior requires a Python binding plus allowlist entry, and narrow “zero routing code” to banks that reuse an existing binding.\n\n4. [§3, §7 C5] “No fallbacks” is not reconciled with existing production fallback behavior. Production currently pads style candidates and falls back to the first chooser candidate (`production_mirror/nodes/_otr_style_picker.py:109-115`, `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_style_picker.py:681-775`), title regen falls back to `outline.title` (`production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:5201-5255`), and announcer outro falls back deterministically (`production_mirror/nodes/_otr_line_composer.py:3595-3601`, `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_line_composer.py:3652-3661`). C5 only names loud non-science failure for `_otr_style_picker` (`input.md:199-201`). Concrete fix: add a fallback inventory and lane policy matrix: preserve only explicitly grandfathered science baseline fallbacks, fail loud for new lanes, and test each named site.\n\nSHOULD-FIX:\n1. [§6, §7 C5] Visual transplant scope is too broad for this round. C5 includes `_otr_story_brief_helpers`, `otr_meta_brief_image_prompt`, `otr_shot_lock`, and `render_driver`-adjacent policy reads (`input.md:201-203`), while the manifest says deep visual prompts are risky and must be staged one by one (`TRANSPLANT_MANIFEST.md:32-47`). Concrete fix: keep only shared-tail policy seams in this build; defer deep render-driver prompt extraction to a separate gated stage.\n\n2. [§7 C2] “Diverged v1 Python/JSON lists reconciled by union” is a weak creative-resolution rule (`input.md:178-180`). A union can preserve contradictory guardrails instead of choosing the correct authorial source. Concrete fix: require a per-seam diff artifact with one chosen winner and a reason; use union only for non-ordered forbidden-term metadata.\n\n3. [§5, §8] [ASSUMPTION] If any mirror/drift/patch tests import production modules, the mirror is incomplete for that. `OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py` imports `._otr_model_catalog` and `._otr_story_brief` (`production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:121-131`), but those files are not in the copied-file manifest (`PRODUCTION_MIRROR_MANIFEST.md:41-66`). Concrete fix: state drift tests are AST-only, or mirror import dependencies before any import smoke.\n\nOPTIONAL / NICE-TO-HAVE:\n- [§7b] Keep provenance hashes, but define `lab_state_digest` deterministically before it becomes a gate (`input.md:225-230`).\n- [§7b] Single-level pack `extends` can stay future-only; do not add it before the basic pack resolution is green (`input.md:244-248`).\n\nCUT THESE (scope / over-engineering):\n1. [§7 C5] Cut production patch specs from tonight. It is safe because C1-C4 already prove the registry, fixtures, bridge artifact, nodes, and validation loop; C5 conflicts with `TRANSPLANT_MANIFEST.md:63-76`.\n\n2. [§3, §9] Cut the adaptive-cleanup experiment from `pipelines.json` entirely for this build. A documented-disabled experiment still expands schema/test surface while the non-goal says no implementation tonight (`input.md:77-79`, `input.md:262-263`).\n\n3. [§7b] Cut exhaustive full Cartesian testing over invalid bank/model/pipeline/style products. Keep the declared compatibility matrix plus one negative test per unknown axis. The plan’s “ALL combos” wording (`input.md:231-237`) risks turning source-scoped story models (`input.md:53-54`) into noisy test bloat."}}
